We have a slider composed of 3 slides, obviously we need to hide the previous button in the first slide and next button in the last slide !--more--

Below is the slider in our template, the full structure of the slider were omitted for brevity 

 ion-slides #slider .../ion-slides
  ion-button Prev /ion-button
  ion-button Next/ion-button

We use ViewChild to get the functionality of our ion-slides as following   
@ViewChild("slider", { static: true }) slider;
Inside the class will add a couple of boolean properties called isNextButtonVisible and isPrevButtonVisible
isNextButtonVisible = true;
isPrevButtonVisible = false;

Let's add a utility function to control the state of those controls, the function is given the slideIndex

 @ViewChild("slider", { static: true }) slider;

  isNextButtonVisible = true;
  isPrevButtonVisible = false;

  prevOrNextButton(slideIndex: number) {
    this.isPrevButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 0;
    this.isNextButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 2;
  }

We will make use of the event slideWillChange()

 ion-slides #slider (ionSlideWillChange)="slideWillChange()"
     ...
 /ion-slides
  ion-button Prev /ion-button
  ion-button Next/ion-button

Inside the slideWillChange() will call prevOrNextButton passing the active slideIndex

  isNextButtonVisible = true;
  isPrevButtonVisible = false;
  prevOrNextButton(slideIndex: number) {
    this.isPrevButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 0;
    this.isNextButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 2;
  }
 slideWillChange() {     
    this.slider.getActiveIndex().then((slideIndex) = {
      this.prevOrNextButton(slideIndex);
    });
  }

 Finally let’s change the template a bit to include the condition for hide/show controls 

  ion-button *ngIf="isPrevButtonVisible" Prev /ion-button
  ion-button  *ngIf="isPrevButtonVisible"Next/ion-button

