If you receive NotSerializableException, in your scripted pipeline or share library, there are couple of reasons: !--more--

Missing @NonCPS annotation

Make sure you add @NonCPS before you code block

@NonCPS
private void showChangeLogs(RunWrapper currentBuild) {
...
}

 Missing def

Make sure there is no def is missing, for example

 for (change in changeLogSets) {
        entries = change.items;
        for (entry in entries) {
          .....
        }
    }

The above code can result in the java.io.NotSerializableException: hudson.plugins.git.GitChangeSet

Rectifying this is just a matter of adding tye missing def before
def entries = change.items;

