List all of the plugins you have in your instance

We will need to use for loop to iterate over the list of Jenkins.instance.pluginManager.plugins and print each plugin name

for(plugin in for(plugin in Jenkins.instance.pluginManager.plugins) {
  println(plugin);
}

To sort the plugins say by alphabetical order, because Jenkins.instance.pluginManager.plugins is read-only we need to clone plugins in a new list .i.e. sortedPlugins

ListString sortedPlugins = new ArrayListString(Jenkins.instance.pluginManager.plugins);
sortedPlugins = sortedPlugins.sort{x - x.displayName.toLowerCase()}
for(plugin in sortedPlugins) {
  println(plugin);
}

 Check if a plugin is installed

def antPlugin = new ArrayListString(Jenkins.instance.pluginManager.plugins).find{x - x.displayName == 'Ant Plugin'};
println(antPlugin == null ? "Not installed" : "Installed" );

We can take this step further and create function, how about isInstalled() with a string displayName argument

Boolean isInstalled(String displayName) {

	def plugin = new ArrayListString(Jenkins.instance.pluginManager.plugins).find{x - x.displayName == displayName};
	return plugin != null;
}

println(isInstalled("Ant Plugin") ?  "Installed" : "Not installed");
